This change ensures that the `trunc` is only inserted when it is a valid and necessary operation, i.e., when the source type is wider than the destination type.

### 5. Conclusion

The root cause of the crash is an incorrect unconditional `trunc` instruction being generated by `VPScalarIVStepsRecipe::execute`. The recipe did not account for cases where the start index and step value for the induction have the same type, leading to an attempt to create an invalid `trunc i32 to i32` cast. By adding a condition to only perform the truncation when the source type is wider than the destination, we fix the assertion failure and allow the vectorizer to correctly generate code for this and similar cases.

